# Foundation Primitives

- Prefer existing primitives before building new UI pieces.
- Do not hardcode replacement components for `Button`, `Text`, `Wrapper`, layout, or head primitives when local fundation components already exist.
- Every public page should have its own page-specific component folder for its sections.
- Keep page files focused on composition: import sections and assemble the page.
- `Wrapper` is required for page section structure unless there is a documented exception.
- Each section owns its own `Wrapper`.
- Do not use one shared `Wrapper` around multiple sections in a page.
- Compose pages from the existing system first; only add a new primitive when the current set cannot express the need cleanly.
- Avoid one-off card, button, and text abstractions that bypass the local fundation layer.
